**Abstract:**
Brief notes titled "Aris' Rhetoric as a Work of Philosophy." Discusses speech-act theory: illocutionary acts, constatives vs. performatives, assertions vs. directives. Questions view that language's basic function is stating true propositions with other uses as deviations. Notes rhetoric is not simple assertion because of inducements. Distinguishes performatives/constatives, assertives/directives, word/world. Mentions declaratives in institutional settings.

**AI Recommendation:** Keep in undated/notes - theoretical notes on speech acts

